It also doesn’t help that `SPX_THROW_ON_FAIL` names its parameter `hr` and uses terms conventionally used with HRESULTs, but apparently Azure Speech Cognitive Service decided to reinvent HRESULTs yet again in a slightly different format, so that assumption didn’t hold.